---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Ergo Sum" description="Privacy policy for Ergo Sum apps.">
  <section class="py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight" data-reveal>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-apple-muted" data-reveal>Last updated: March 15, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-12 text-lg leading-relaxed text-apple-muted">
        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Ergo Sum ("we", "us", "our") builds apps designed to respect your privacy.
            This policy covers all apps published by Ergo Sum, including Midnight Society and Aerie.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Midnight Society</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">Data stored on your device:</strong> Midnight Society
            stores your profile name, avatar symbol, avatar color, optional profile photo, and game
            state locally on your device using UserDefaults. This data is not transmitted to our
            servers or any third party.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">Local network communication:</strong> Midnight Society
            uses Apple's MultipeerConnectivity framework to discover and connect nearby players over
            your local WiFi network (Bonjour/mDNS). This communication is peer-to-peer, stays
            entirely on your local network, and no data is sent to external servers.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">In-app purchases:</strong> All purchase processing is
            handled natively through Apple's StoreKit 2 framework. No third-party payment or analytics
            SDKs are involved. Apple processes all transactions and handles payment data per their
            own <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy policy</a>.
            Purchase history is cached locally on your device for convenience; the App Store is the
            source of truth.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">Third parties:</strong> Midnight Society does not share
            data with any third-party services, analytics providers, or advertisers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Aerie</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">Data stored on your device:</strong> All thoughts and
            notes are stored locally on your device and are not transmitted to our servers.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-apple-text">Third parties:</strong> Aerie does not share data with
            any third-party services, analytics providers, or advertisers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">General Practices</h2>
          <ul class="mt-4 list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
            <li>We do not currently collect personal information.</li>
            <li>We do not currently use analytics or tracking tools.</li>
            <li>We do not serve advertisements.</li>
            <li>We do not sell or share data with third parties.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Data Deletion</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            In Midnight Society, you can delete your profile from within the app. To remove all app
            data completely, delete and reinstall the app. Since all data is stored locally on your
            device, no server-side deletion is necessary.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            In Aerie, deleting the app removes all stored data. No server-side deletion is necessary.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Our apps are not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information
            from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has provided us with personal
            information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected by
            updating the "last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of our apps
            after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-apple-text">Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-4">
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:support@ergosum.studio" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">support@ergosum.studio</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
